    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Playoff History</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By MIKE WISE</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Wise, Mike</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Previous two times New York Knickerbockers lost Game 1 of playoff series they went on to lose series (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The previous two times the Knicks lost Game 1 of a playoff series, they went on to lose the series. In the 1999 finals against San Antonio, they were beaten soundly by the Spurs in Game 1 and went on to lose the series in five games.</p>
        <p>The same thing happened against Indiana in the second round of the 1998 playoffs. But there is also a recent example of coming back from a Game 1 loss and winning a series.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The previous two times the Knicks lost Game 1 of a playoff series, they went on to lose the series. In the 1999 finals against San Antonio, they were beaten soundly by the Spurs in Game 1 and went on to lose the series in five games.</p>
        <p>The same thing happened against Indiana in the second round of the 1998 playoffs. But there is also a recent example of coming back from a Game 1 loss and winning a series.</p>
        <p>In 1998 the Knicks lost Game 1 of their first-round series to the Heat at Miami Arena. They went on to win in five games.</p>
        <p>MIKE WISE</p>
        <p>PRO BASKETBALL: NOTEBOOK</p>
